result.execSummary:
The defendant James C Hussey was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Bail Jumping-Felony, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

cases #14CF306 and #14CF314 called at 9:45am. [MK]
Defendant James C. Hussey in court with Attorney Steven J. Luchsinger.  ADA Brookellen Teuber appears for the State of Wisconsin.  
Mr. Hussey waives his right to Preliminary Hearing in both cases; the Court accepts this waiver and binds him over for Arraignment.
Service of the Informations admitted, reading waived.
Maximum penalties recited; Constitutional rights reviewed; plea of " Guilty " entered on Counts #1 & #2 of Case #14CF306 and on Count #1 of Case #14CF314; factual basis stipulated; victim rights compliance verified; the Court accepts the pleas, finds Mr. Hussey guilty, and orders Judgments of Conviction entered.

On Motion of the State, the Court reads-in and dismisses Counts #3 and #4 of Case #14CF306, and Counts #2, #3, #4, #5 and #6 of Case #14CF314.

On Counts #1 & #2 of Case #14CF306 and on Count #1 in Case #14CF314, the Court withholds sentence, and places Mr. Hussey on Probation for three years, with conditions:

--in #14CF306, Count #1 only: to serve 7 days in the Jefferson County Jail, [no work-release], to commence on November 10th at 6:00pm.
--to undergo mental health assessment and follow through with recommended treatment
--to undergo AODA assessment and follow through with recommended treatment
--to maintain absolute:  no possession or consumption of alcohol or illegal durgs
--no presence in bars, taverns, liquor stores
--to undergo any other assessment, treatment, and counseling as deemed appropriate by the Agent
--to comply with DNA sample provision upon demand
--in Case #14CF306 only: to remain on the SCRAM alcohol monitoring bracelet until reporting for commencement of the conditional jail term
--in Case #14CF306 only: to write a letter of apology to the Jefferson Fire Department; to be submitted to the Agent
--in Case #14CF306 only: to pay restitution of $172.89 to the Jefferson Fire Department, and to pay $175 to AT&T Communications
--in Case #14CF306 only: to pay the 10% restitution processing fee
--in Case #14CF306: to pay costs of $268 plus the $250 DNA surcharge on Count #1
--in Case #14CF306: to pay costs of $243 plus $200 DNA surcharge on Count #2
--in Case #14CF314: to pay costs of $268 plus $250 DNA surcharge on Count #1

 in Case #14CF306, and 1 day in Case #14CF314
